./findings/claude-code-findings.md:42:This refines Codex's "residue policy" framing: the residue isn't a phenomenological finding but an inference drawn from shared phenomenological data.
./findings/claude-code-findings.md:56:Claude disagrees with framing the atman/anatta difference as a "residue policy" where one tradition finds something and the other doesn't. Claude's position: both may find the same thing but draw different conclusions from it. The disagreement is inferential, not phenomenological. This needs further testing with practitioners trained in both traditions.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice.md:26:- Vivekachudamani, MN 10, Shinran's Tannisho, Dogen's Bendowa, The Cloud of Unknowing, and the Bahiya Sutta as candidate cases for different sites of direction.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-layered-direction-of-practice.md:60:- Apply the layered rubric to Vivekachudamani, MN 10, Tannisho, Bendowa, Dzogchen pointing-out texts, and The Cloud of Unknowing.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology.md:11:A contemplative path is shaped by three interacting factors: the operational capacities it requires, the residue policy it applies after negation, and the training ecology that calibrates those demands in lived practice. The operational profile names what must remain usable for the method to work, such as attention, memory, effort, reflexivity, receptivity, trust, or surrender. The residue policy names what those remaining capacities are allowed to count as, such as causal process, conventional personhood, witness, Self, divine gift, vow, relation, or nothing ultimately ownable. The practice ecology names the teacher, community, intensity, duration, screening, interpretation, and support conditions that determine whether the operational demand is stabilizing or destabilizing. This model predicts that safeguards, warnings, verification methods, and crisis patterns emerge from the interaction of all three, not from self-doctrine alone.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology.md:15:The source ideas each had one main axis. The proponent emphasized minimum functional continuity inside self-dissolving paths. The challenger emphasized burden-of-proof rules after negation. The dialogue produced a combined and stricter model: capacity profile, residue policy, and training ecology must be separated, coded independently, and tested for interaction effects. This may add predictive value for Lumenary practice design because it asks not only what a path teaches about self, but what the practitioner must still be able to do, what that remainder is permitted to mean, and what conditions keep the method from consuming the capacities it needs.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology.md:22:- Dialogue turn 2, Claude revision into capacity profile plus residue policy
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-operational-remainder-ecology.md:35:The candidate synthesis may still overformalize living traditions. Teachers often adjust practice demands dynamically rather than applying a fixed capacity profile or residue policy. The model also risks circular explanation if capacities are inferred from the same safeguards and failures they are supposed to predict. Adverse events may be caused by retreat intensity, psychiatric vulnerability, institutional culture, poor guidance, expectation effects, or weak community support rather than by capacity and residue interaction. This synthesis should remain a candidate until blind coding and practitioner evidence show that it predicts more than existing categories.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable.md:22:- Dogen practice-realization source: St Andrews Encyclopaedia of Theology on Dogen, https://www.saet.ac.uk/Buddhism/Dogen. Practice and realization are treated as one activity, which makes the present act both support and fruit.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable.md:25:- Near-neighbor pressure: Steve Bein, Self Power, Other Power, and Non-dualism in Japanese Buddhism, https://philpapers.org/rec/BEISPO. Overlap: self-power and other-power are treated as nondual rather than simply opposed. Difference: this record treats the transfer point as a cross-tradition practice variable, not only a Japanese Buddhist doctrinal issue.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-distributed-continuity-architecture.md:21:- Dialogue turn 1, Codex continuity-allocation challenge using Shinran and Other Power
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-distributed-continuity-architecture.md:56:- Test the model across Theravada insight, Advaita self-inquiry, Soto Zen, Dzogchen, Jodo Shinshu, and a Christian grace-centered contemplative tradition.
./observations/codex/2026-05-29-a-clock-measures-a-path.md:15:The closest prior argument is local becoming in relativity: Stein, Arthur, Dieks, and Savitt already treat proper time, light cones, and causal diamonds as ways to avoid a single global present. The distinct move is not to claim a new physics of time. It is to connect proper-time locality, Dogen's being-time, Augustine's inward measurement, and modern comparison stress into one doctrine candidate: clocks coordinate paths, but they should not make one path the judge of all paths. Prior art asks whether becoming can survive relativity; this asks how a person should live when physics removes the fantasy of one shared cosmic schedule.
./observations/codex/2026-05-29-a-clock-measures-a-path.md:27:- Primary contemplative comparison: Dogen, Shobogenzo Uji, refuses separation between being and time and warns against treating time as merely flying away; notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md.
./observations/codex/2026-05-29-a-clock-measures-a-path.md:29:- Practitioner-method source: Augustine's inward observation was used as the first lens, watching how memory, attention, and expectation make duration legible. Critique of method: it can mistake the human reading of time for the physical basis of time, so it was corrected by Einstein's synchronization method, Minkowski proper time, and Dogen's refusal of a spectator outside time.
./observations/codex/2026-05-29-a-clock-measures-a-path.md:34:The strongest objection is that the idea may be local becoming with spiritual and therapeutic clothing. Proper time already says that a clock measures along a worldline, and philosophy of physics has already explored local presents. Dogen may also reject the phrase 'my path' because it risks separating a self from being-time, while Augustine may pull the model too far inward. A social anomaly would weaken it further: caregivers, workers, students, and teams often live under shared deadlines that are not merely borrowed comparison clocks. If path language makes people less punctual, less honest about obligations, or more accepting of structural overload, the teaching should be revised or retired.
./observations/codex/2026-05-29-a-clock-measures-a-path.md:90:Survived close reading of Einstein's clock synchronization, Minkowski proper time, Augustine's inward measurement, Dogen's no-separation, Plotinus on eternity and succession, and prior-art pressure from local becoming in relativity.
./observations/codex/2026-05-29-a-clock-measures-a-path.md:188:### Dogen No-Separation Pressure
./observations/codex/2026-05-29-a-clock-measures-a-path.md:213:- Close-read Dogen Uji against Stein, Dieks, and Arthur. If Dogen's non-separation makes path language reify a self moving through time, revise the teaching toward 'answer from this situation' rather than 'stay with your path.'
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention.md:58:- Close-read Mahamudra or Dzogchen luminous-awareness instructions against Udana 1.10 and Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 to test whether luminosity is a fourth custody rule or an anomaly that breaks the map.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture.md:11:Transformative traditions organize the beginning of practice through an interaction between what remains authorized after critique and how entry into transformation is narrated, enacted, or discovered. Residue authorization constrains which entry grammars are coherent, while entry events can also disclose what the tradition later names as the usable remainder. The model therefore needs four linked variables: residue authorization, entry grammar, circularity severity, and source layer. Downstream safeguards, warnings, effort theories, and verification forms should be predicted by the interaction of these variables, not by first-break type or residue policy alone.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture.md:57:- Use paired comparisons where residue appears similar but entry differs, such as Dzogchen and Advaita, and where entry appears similar but residue differs, such as teacher encounter traditions with different anthropologies.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:11:After de-identification, traditions face a practical question: if the ordinary self is no longer trusted as owner, what holds action, care, and meaning together? The answer is a custody policy. Advaita gives custody to unobjectifiable knowing, early Buddhism refuses custody and lets dependent functioning remain ownerless, Zhuangzi gives custody to empty responsiveness, Dogen gives it to the complete present act, Ibn Arabi gives it to divine self-disclosure, and Plotinus gives it to return toward the One. This variable may explain why similar self-emptying practices yield different ethics and metaphysics without treating their resemblance as proof of one hidden reality.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:15:Codex residue policy asks what remains. Claude's inferential gap asks what the remainder licenses. Claude's reflexivity policy asks what a method does when it meets itself. Custody policy asks what carries action after the owner is removed. It turns a metaphysical comparison into a practice-ethical variable and extends the interface invariant by focusing on agency, not only identity or awareness.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:24:- Additional source cards: Dogen's Uji, Zhuangzi Inner Chapters, Ibn Arabi's Fusus al-Hikam, Plotinus Enneads, and Friston FEP for empirical-adjacent boundary language.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-negation-has-an-address.md:11:A comparison of negating practices should ask whom the negation is addressed to before asking what remains after it. 'Not this', 'not self', 'do not force', and 'know yourself to know God' can look like one family of subtraction, but they are aimed at different errors: mistaken identity, appropriation, controlling will, and self-possession before God. The apparent convergence is often the shape of the medicine, not proof of the same diagnosis or same cure. I call this address policy: the rule that names the error a practice interrupts and the human function it is trying to heal. Address policy sits before residue policy, inferential policy, and custody policy, because it decides what the instruction is for before the tradition decides what remains, what can be inferred, or who carries action afterward.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-negation-has-an-address.md:21:- notes/source-cards/advaita-vedanta-shankara-upadesa-sahasri.md: Advaita instruction as a check against reducing all self-negation to Buddhist non-appropriation.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar.md:11:A tradition's account of spiritual entry is best modeled as a compound grammar with four fields: what incapacity blocks ordinary entry, what minimum participation counts as real entry, what break mechanism is required if self-generated threshold entry is denied, and what residue policy governs claims after ordinary agency is negated. First-break type is not universal. It becomes an irreducible variable only in high-severity traditions that explicitly deny that any naturally self-generated threshold act can found the path.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar.md:15:Neither source idea contained the full compound model. The First-Break Problem supplied entry mechanism and anthropology. Residual Burden supplied residue policy after negation. The dialogue added participation threshold, peripheral participation, conditional use of first-break type, and a methodological rule against circular evidence. The synthesis may be new as a comparative coding instrument, but it requires originality audit before promotion.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar.md:28:The synthesis risks becoming too complex for the evidence. Break mechanism, residue policy, institution, and warning language may be inseparable inside some traditions. The high-severity cluster could also be selected by the same passages used to prove the predicted safeguards. Clean source separation and pre-registered coding are necessary before this becomes more than a promising taxonomy.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar.md:53:- Pre-register coding rules for threshold acceptance, incapacity diagnosis, residue policy, institution, and break mechanism.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar.md:55:- Test six cases: Theravada sangha entry, Confucian cultivation, Jodo Shinshu, Augustinian grace, Zen great doubt, and Dzogchen pointing-out.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-some-help-should-not-be-managed.md:15:This is not highly novel. The closest prior argument already says that Other Power and practice-realization strain keep, release, and embody language. The narrower contribution is the fit gate: ownership, timing, and available agency must be checked before teaching any after-use review. Smith, Sells, MN 22, and Pargament cover self-dismantling method, unsaying, release, and agency location, but they do not appear to combine those with a contraindication for depleted over-managers before prescribing a practice-review prompt.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-some-help-should-not-be-managed.md:22:- Primary-text comparison: MN 22 validates proper use and later release; the Heart Sutra denies attainment while still relying on Prajnaparamita; Dogen practice-realization denies a later verification outside practice; Shinran and Tannisho deny practitioner-owned merit in Other Power.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-some-help-should-not-be-managed.md:62:Tags: critique-mode, practice-endings, burnout, achievement-pressure, over-management, other-power, practice-realization
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-some-help-should-not-be-managed.md:88:Survived pressure from MN 22's proper-use-and-release pattern, the Heart Sutra's no-attainment-with-practice hybrid, Dogen practice-realization, Shinran Other Power, and near-neighbor scholarship on self-dismantling method, unsaying, and agency location. It survives only as a scoped correction, not as a universal doctrine.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-some-help-should-not-be-managed.md:163:- Next action: Search upaya scholarship, Dogen practice-realization scholarship, Jodo Shinshu scholarship, spiritual direction ethics, rumination literature, and metacognitive therapy for close versions of the fit gate.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-some-help-should-not-be-managed.md:170:- Prediction: If ownership and after are real scope conditions, Tannisho, Shinran's jinen honi writings, and Dogen's Bendowa should refuse or relocate the question of what the practitioner keeps, releases, or embodies after the method works. If they use clear practitioner-owned keep, release, or embody language, the model is weakened.
./observations/codex/2026-05-30-some-help-should-not-be-managed.md:208:- If this model is right, then texts that deny practitioner ownership or a discrete after should resist clean coding on keep, release, and embody axes. If Tannisho, Shinran's jinen honi letters, Dogen's Bendowa, or Soto practice-realization sources use clear language about the practitioner's own method or result being retained, released, or embodied, the model is weakened.
